							<article class=3D"detail-wrapper d-none">
							  <p>
							  	Creating an online survey might sound like a simple endeavor =E2=
=80=93 you just come up with questions, input them, and hit send, right? Bu=
t building a successful survey that attracts respondents, engages them, and=
 provides rich data and insights requires a lot of time, thought, and plann=
ing.=20
 Here are seven tips for what to consider when you=E2=80=99re putting toget=
her your next survey:=20
1. Plan your survey comprehensively
 When coming up with your survey, it can be easy to focus on the content of=
 the questions and the types of responses you hope to receive. But thinking=
 ahead and considering how you=E2=80=99ll analyze the survey data can help =
you craft questions, tweak response options and formats, and ensure your su=
rvey is as efficient and successful as possible. By planning your analysis =
and keeping in mind the type of data you=E2=80=99d like to have at the end =
of your survey=E2=80=93 be it summary tables, visualizations, or statistica=
l tests =E2=80=93 you can optimize your questionnaire in small ways that ca=
n have a big impact on your results.=20
 Good to know: With LimeSurvey it's easy to export your survey responses as=
 different data formats, including Excel as well as dedicated survey softwa=
re like R or SPSS Statistics.=20
2. Respect privacy and data protection
 Ensuring your survey is compliant with data protection laws like GDPR and =
guaranteeing privacy can help assuage respondents=E2=80=99 concerns about h=
ow their responses will be used. This assurance can also go a long way in e=
ncouraging them to provide their honest thoughts and true point of view.=20
 Good to know: Relevant privacy features like anonymous responses or encryp=
tion and data protection come out of the box with LimeSurvey Cloud and can =
be configured according to your needs.=20
3. Know your target audience
 Whether you=E2=80=99re launching an employee satisfaction survey for your =
direct team or a customer satisfaction survey for hundreds of thousands of =
active customers, it=E2=80=99s important to know precisely who your target =
audience is. If you=E2=80=99re only seeking feedback from a small number of=
 people, this is usually a simple task, but if you=E2=80=99re dealing with =
a large number of possible respondents, one best practice is to draw a samp=
le of the relevant audience you=E2=80=99d like to hear back from, and invit=
e those people.=20
 If you are conducting an exploratory study and do not have a list of all p=
ossible respondents available, considering how to target relevant responden=
ts is critical. If you need results that are representative of the general =
population, it=E2=80=99s best to avoid river sampling, or recruiting survey=
 participants while they are carrying out another online activity. Dependin=
g on your field of research, partnering with a panel provider who can help =
you reach relevant respondents might be the best way forward,=20
 Good to know: LimeSurvey offers panel integration that makes it easy to in=
clude respondents from professional panel providers.=20
 Get started with LimeSurvey=20
4. Tailor your questionnaire to participants
 One great thing about online questionnaires is that you can create an indi=
vidual survey experience for every participant, when needed. With informati=
on you=E2=80=99ve already gathered about each respondent and/or their previ=
ous answers, you can use LimeSurvey=E2=80=99s integrated condition designer=
 and expression manager to filter pages, questions, and response options, a=
s well as create individual texts and provide direct feedback. This is espe=
cially useful if participants are completing an assessment or providing con=
structive criticism of a course, experience, or service. With these feature=
s, your questionnaire becomes not just another boring survey, but an immers=
ive experience that motivates respondents to provide accurate responses.=20
5. Monitor survey responses
 While it might seem prudent to wait to look at your survey responses until=
 it has closed, it can be beneficial to keep an eye on responses while the =
survey is ongoing. By checking data during field time, you=E2=80=99ll know =
early if there are any problems with the questionnaire and whether or not y=
ou need to follow-up with respondents, reminding them to take the survey.=
=20
 Good to know: LimeSurvey offers users direct access to their survey respon=
ses, so you can keep an eye on your data without having to export it.=20
6. Implement measures to obtain high data quality
 Before beginning your data analysis, it=E2=80=99s important that you check=
 the quality of the data. This helps exclude incomplete or duplicate survey=
s as well as surveys containing implausible or quick responses, so that you=
r results are not skewed by errors.=20
 To help identify participants who are not taking your questionnaire seriou=
sly, you can include special questions that can help you pinpoint a respond=
ent=E2=80=99s motivation, or use LimeSurvey=E2=80=99s quote feature, which =
excludes participants who fail your quality test.=20
7. Work to achieve high response rates
 Though you may not receive a 100% participation rate for your questionnair=
e, there are ways to motivate people to participate. Chief among them is ma=
king sure that you give people enough time to respond. If your field time i=
s too short, that will have a significant impact on participation and data,=
 and can result in a biased sample composition. Another great way to encour=
age participation is to follow-up with them =E2=80=93 with LimeSurvey=E2=80=
=99s closed-access surveys, you can send reminders to people who have not s=
tarted your survey, as well as those who have started but have yet to finis=
h.=20
 Good to know: LimeSurvey offers the option to save and resume a questionna=
ire for both closed-access and open-access surveys.=20
 By keeping these seven pointers in mind while planning your survey, you ca=
n ensure your timelines are sound, optimize your questionnaire, and set you=
rself up for success.=20
 With LimeSurvey, you can create and customize surveys that suit your needs=
. For more information on getting started or using our vast array of tools,=
 check out our robust Help Center.=20

 Get started with LimeSurvey							  </p>
